The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Varun hope
                                                                                                               Varun hope
                            
	New Delhi, April 13 (PTI): Varun Gandhi may get a reprieve with the Supreme Court today suggesting that he give an undertaking to stop making provocative speeches if granted interim bail.        
	Varun, the BJP candidate from Pilibhit in Uttar Pradesh, has agreed to do so. His counsel Mukul Rohtagi said Varun would give the undertaking. The hearing has been adjourned till April 16.                                                                                                                                                                                    
